A_n := \begin{pmatrix} a_n \\ a_{n+1} \\ \vdots \\ a_{n+k-1} \end{pmatrix} 
  A_{n+1} = \begin{pmatrix} a_{n+1} \\ a_{n+2} \\ \vdots \\ a_{n+k} \end{pmatrix}    = \underbrace{\begin{pmatrix} 0 & 1 & 0 & \cdots & 0\\ 0 &0 & 1 & \cdots & 0\\ \vdots & \vdots & \vdots & \ddots & \vdots \\ b_0 & b_1 & b_2 &\cdots & b_{k-1}\end{pmatrix}}_{M:=} \cdot \begin{pmatrix} a_n \\ a_{n+1} \\ \vdots \\ a_{n+k-1} \end{pmatrix}  = M\cdot A_n  
 A_n = M^n \cdot A_0 = M^n \cdot\begin{pmatrix} a_0 \\ a_1 \\ \vdots \\ a_{k-1} \end{pmatrix} 
